This is a modal window. Beginning of dialog window. Escape will cancel and close the window. End of dialog window. Africa’s premier Mixed Martial Arts, MMA, promotion One Fight Ultimate, OFU, is set to ignite the sprawling city of Ajegunle in Lagos in continuation of its Streetfight series, as Four MMA gladiators take the ring on Sunday. The eagerly anticipated outdoor professional tournament themed AJ City Rumble has got  fans in Ajegunle and beyond salivating for what promises to be a show stopper at Navy Barracks from 3PM with free entry. Four MMA gladiators have a challenge of fighting through three bouts, tournament style, to be crowned the OFU Ultimate street fighter. According to the Organisers, “the choice of staging the championship in Ajegunle which means land of riches in the Yoruba language of South Western Nigeria is instructive owing to the sporting and entertainment history of the area, inhabited by more than half a million Lagosians. “Today some of the OFU3 Street fighters are raring to make a name for themselves just like the footballers; this time around, in MMA. ‘Benue Boi’ Victor Dooga who faces ‘The Skull’ Geoffrey John in one of the semi final matchups has a huge fan base in Ajegunle where he trains: “Already my AJ fans are looking forward to my fight at Navy Barracks. “My gym has spread the word to the community that I will be fighting on 1st May and ever since, I have been getting numerous calls from them, enquiring about my training and state of health.